  "label": "The Ledgerhouse Berthbay",
  "description": "The Ledgerhouse Berthbay is a narrow sleeping compartment partitioned from the habitation suite by a sliding plasteel bulkhead stamped with service numerals. Two stacked bunks are bolted directly to the deck and wall frame, their restraint straps and under-bunk drawers designed for sealed living under alert conditions. A low, constant lumen strip runs the ceiling edge, throwing hard light across scuffed panels and redundant conduit covers. Vent grilles and a compact alarm-vox plate dominate the headwall, reinforcing the enclave’s doctrine of blackout, rationing, and rapid muster.",
